# League DB

League DB is an API allowing players and fans of League of Legends to view different
kinds of information. All data will be in the JSON format.

## Champions [/api/champions]

### Get All Champions [GET]

Get information about every champion.

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        [
            {
                "name": "aatrox",
                "role": "top",
                "region": "unknown",
                "items": [
                    "bladeoftheruinedking",
                    "deathsdance",
                    ...
                ],
                "image":"https://ddragon.leagueoflegends.com/cdn/7.12.1/img/champion/Aatrox.png"
            },
            {
                "name": "ahri",
                "role": "mid",
                "region": "ionia",
                "items": [
                    "morellonomicon",
                    "ludensecho",
                    ...
                ],
                "image": "https://ddragon.leagueoflegends.com/cdn/7.12.1/img/champion/Ahri.png"
            },
            ...
        ]

### Get A Champion By Name [GET /api/champions/{name}]

Get information about one champion by using a name parameter, which must contain only 
lowercase letters.

+ Parameters
    + name: draven

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        [
            {
                "name": "draven",
                "role": "bot",
                "region": "noxus",
                "items": [
                    "deathsdance",
                    "statikkshiv",
                    ...
                ],
                "image": "https://ddragon.leagueoflegends.com/cdn/7.12.1/img/champion/Draven.png"
            }
        ]

## Regions [/api/regions]

### Get Regions [GET]

Get information of all of the regions of lore in the League of Legends universe.

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        [
            {
                "name": "ionia",
                "champions": "top",
                "items": "",
                "lore": "",
                "image":"/images/ionia"
            },
            {
                "name": "noxus",
                "champions": "top",
                "items": "",
                "lore": "",
                "image":"/images/noxus"
            },
            ...
        ]

### Get A Region by Name [GET /api/regions/{name}]

Get information about a region with a name parameter, which must contain only 
lowercase letters.

+ Parameters
    + name: noxus

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        [
            {
                "name": "noxus",
                "champions": [
                    "cassiopeia",
                    "draven",
                ],
                "image":""
            }
        ]

